The paper addresses the problem of instance-level semantic segmentation, which is a task in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new network architecture and uses deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on two datasets, PASCAL VOC 2012 and Cityscapes, which are commonly used in computer vision research, indicating that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.RO (Robotics).
